  "prompt": "How many people graduate in India every year (with at least a bachelors degree)?",
  "response": "As of the latest available data up to 2023, India graduates approximately **1 million (10 lakh)** students each year with at least a bachelor's degree. This number reflects the rapid expansion and growth of India's higher education sector over recent years. \n\n**Key Points:**\n\n1. **Higher Education Growth:** India's higher education system has been expanding significantly, with an increasing number of universities, colleges, and technical institutes contributing to the higher graduation rates.\n\n2. **Diverse Fields:** Graduates emerge from a wide range of disciplines, including engineering, technology, medicine, arts, commerce, and sciences, catering to the diverse economic and industrial needs of the country.\n\n3. **Government Initiatives:** Various government initiatives and policies aimed at improving access to higher education, such as the expansion of online education platforms and increased funding for educational institutions, have contributed to the rise in graduation numbers.\n\n4. **Future Projections:** The trend suggests a continued increase in the number of graduates annually, driven by both governmental support and the private sector's investment in education.\n\n**Sources for Further Reference:**\n\n- **All India Survey on Higher Education (AISHE):** Conducted by the Ministry of Education, Government of India, AISHE provides detailed statistics on higher education trends in the country.\n  \n- **University Grants Commission (UGC):** The UGC regularly publishes reports and data on higher education institutions and graduate numbers across India.\n\nPlease note that exact figures can vary based on the source and the specific year of reporting. For the most precise and up-to-date information, referring to official publications from the Ministry of Education or the University Grants Commission is recommended.",
